directions: In a medium saucepan, saute chicken in oil over medium high heat for 3 minutes or until white. Stir in chili powder and cumin to coat chicken. Saute 3-4 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; heat through.
ingredients: 1 tablespoon canola oil or extra virgin olive oil
10 ounces boneless, skinless chicken breast, cut in bite-sized pieces
1 (15 ounce) can no-salt-added black or red beans
1 cup yellow whole-kernel corn, frozen or canned
Salt and cayenne pepper, to taste
title: Fifteen Minute Chicken Chili
